data.race_name: William Hill Keep Your Raceday Positive Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)

prev_owners.owner: Dee L'Estrange & Mrs Caren Walsh & John F Doyle

runners.comment: Reliable since joining P Kirby; reasonable chance assuming he handles this extra yardage.
runners.spotlight: Ex-Gordon Elliott; off the mark at Market Rasen (2m2f maiden, good) on second start for this trainer, and runner-up to a progressive rival at Uttoxeter (2m4f) since; reasonable chance assuming that he's effective over this longer trip.

runners.comment: Point & bumper winner; made a winning hurdles debut at Wexford (3m) recently; key player.
runners.spotlight: Point and bumper winner; easily justified favouritism on hurdles debut at Wexford (3m maiden; good to yielding) a fortnight ago; penalised accordingly but trainer usually does well with his British runners (2-4 at Cartmel this season); likely to have plenty more to offer with conditions to suit.

stable_tour.quote: We really loved the way he won his point-to-point, coming from off the pace in a slowly run race, and he was impressive when winning a bumper at Killarney in July. He's grown a lot since then so we've given him time. He's only four so we'll probably go for a winners' bumper, and that will dictate where he heads after that. The plan is to go hurdling in the summer as he likes nice ground. 21-11-22

He won his point-to-point at Broughshane and his debut for us was even more impressive when winning a Killarney bumper. That was back in July and he hasn't been out since, but he's training well, and he'll reappear in a Punchestown bumper or at the Scottish National meeting. I think he could be very nice, but he's still a baby. Good ground will suit him and he'll go hurdling in the summer. 06-04-23

runners.comment: Ex-pointer (1-11); failed to build on fair stable/rules debut when toiling at Worcester.
runners.spotlight: 1-11 in Irish points; fair stable/rules debut fourth of six at Market Rasen (2m7f, good) but failed to build on that when toiling under this 7lb claimer at Worcester (2m4f, good) recently; others have stronger credentials.

runners.comment: Hasn't shown anything of note over hurdles (0-6); returning from near three-month absence.
runners.spotlight: Hasn't shown anything of note over hurdles (0-6); takes a marked step back up in distance on return from a near three-month absence; his County Kerry-based trainer is 7-39 (18%) at Cartmel over the past five years.

prev_owners.owner: Let's Get Ready To Rumble Partnership

runners.comment: Won twice on AW (2m) for A King earlier this year; has since changed hands for £11,000.
